<Layout title="Community Guidelines & Moderation - Sojorn" description="What's allowed on Sojorn, how we moderate, and what happens when content is flagged">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-egyptianBlue">Community Guidelines &amp; Moderation Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: February 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p class="lead font-semibold">Sojorn exists to connect friends and communities in a space that respects your dignity, your privacy, and your intelligence. These guidelines define what belongs here and what doesn't. By using Sojorn, you agree to follow them.</p>

      <!-- ─── HOW WE MODERATE ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">How We Moderate</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">All public content on Sojorn (posts, comments, quips, board entries, and group messages in non-encrypted groups) passes through a two-layer moderation system:</p>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3 text-egyptianBlue">Layer 1: Local AI</h3>
        <p class="mb-2">An open-source language model (<strong>LLaMA Guard</strong>) runs directly on our own server hardware. Text analysis happens entirely within our infrastructure.</p>
        <p class="font-semibold text-egyptianBlue">Your content never leaves our servers for this layer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3 text-egyptianBlue">Layer 2: SightEngine</h3>
        <p class="mb-2">A dedicated content moderation API that handles image and text analysis as a secondary check. SightEngine is a specialized moderation service &mdash; not a general-purpose AI company. They exist solely to classify content for safety.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>No model training on your content.</strong> SightEngine's <a href="https://sightengine.com/policies/terms" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Terms of Service</a> (Section 4.5) explicitly prohibit using submitted content to train machine learning models.</li>
          <li><strong>You own your data.</strong> SightEngine acquires no right, title, or interest in your content (Section 9.1). They receive only a limited, revocable license to process it for moderation.</li>
          <li><strong>GDPR compliant.</strong> SightEngine operates under a Data Processing Addendum (DPA) and is compliant with the EU General Data Protection Regulation. They also comply with the Digital Services Act and UK Online Safety Bill.</li>
          <li><strong>Encrypted in transit.</strong> All communication uses TLS 1.3 with A-rated cipher suites. Their infrastructure follows a zero-trust architecture where no network segments are trusted by default.</li>
          <li><strong>ISO 27001 &amp; SOC 2.</strong> SightEngine's data center partners maintain ISO 27001 certification and SOC 2 compliance.</li>
          <li><strong>Immediate deletion available.</strong> Content can be deleted immediately upon processing completion, preventing prolonged retention.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">Full policies: <a href="https://sightengine.com/policies/privacy" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a> &middot; <a href="https://sightengine.com/policies/terms" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Terms of Service</a> &middot; <a href="https://sightengine.com/security" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Security &amp; Compliance</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Fail-Open Fallback</h3>
        <p>If both moderation layers are temporarily unavailable, content is published and flagged for later review. We do not block you from posting because of a system outage.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="mb-4"><strong>Private encrypted messages are never moderated.</strong> End-to-end encrypted conversations (DMs and Capsule groups) cannot be read by our systems.</p>

      <p class="mb-4">When content is flagged, a human moderator reviews the decision. You are notified and can appeal any moderation action through the in-app appeal process.</p>

      <!-- ─── SCORING ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">How Content Is Scored</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Our moderation system evaluates content against three categories we call the <strong>Three Poisons</strong> (a framework borrowed from Buddhist philosophy):</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Hate (dosa)</strong> &mdash; violence, discrimination, threats, sexual exploitation, weapons</li>
        <li><strong>Greed (lobha)</strong> &mdash; scams, spam, financial exploitation, MLM schemes</li>
        <li><strong>Delusion (moha)</strong> &mdash; manipulation, toxicity, deliberate misinformation designed to harm</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">Each category produces a score from 0 to 1. Content scoring above our thresholds is either flagged for human review or labeled as sensitive (NSFW). Content that clearly violates our rules is removed automatically and the poster is notified.</p>

      <!-- ─── WHAT'S NOT ALLOWED ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-red-700">What Is NOT Allowed</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">The following content will be removed and may result in account suspension or permanent ban. There are no warnings for the most severe categories.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Violence &amp; Weapons</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Threats of violence against any person or group</li>
        <li>Content glorifying, promoting, or instructing violence</li>
        <li>Firearms, explosives, or weapon promotion of any kind</li>
        <li>Gore, graphic violence, or content depicting real harm to people or animals</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Sexual Exploitation</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Non-consensual intimate imagery (revenge porn, deepfakes, hidden recordings)</li>
        <li>Sexual exploitation or trafficking content</li>
        <li>Solicitation of sexual services</li>
        <li>Sexually explicit content involving or appearing to involve minors &mdash; <strong>zero tolerance, immediate permanent ban, and report to NCMEC</strong></li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Child Safety</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Any content that sexualizes, endangers, or exploits minors in any way</li>
        <li>Grooming behavior or attempts to contact minors for inappropriate purposes</li>
        <li>Sharing personal information about minors without parental consent</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 font-semibold text-red-700">Sojorn has a strict 18+ age requirement. Violations of child safety rules result in immediate and permanent removal with no appeal, and are reported to the appropriate authorities.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Hard Drugs</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Promotion, sale, or instruction for manufacturing of hard drugs (cocaine, heroin, methamphetamine, fentanyl, etc.)</li>
        <li>Content glorifying hard drug use or encouraging others to try hard drugs</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Financial Exploitation</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Scams, phishing, or fraudulent schemes of any kind</li>
        <li>Multi-level marketing (MLM) recruitment or promotion</li>
        <li>Pyramid schemes, Ponzi schemes, or any deceptive financial structures</li>
        <li>Fake investment opportunities, pump-and-dump crypto schemes, or get-rich-quick promotions</li>
        <li>Gambling promotion or gambling-related content</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Religious Exploitation</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Using religious authority, language, or community trust to manipulate, recruit, or extract money from users</li>
        <li>Cult recruitment or high-control group promotion</li>
        <li>Faith-based scams (prosperity gospel grifts, fake charity solicitation, etc.)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">For clarity: sincere religious expression and discussion is welcome. Exploiting faith to manipulate people is not.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Harassment &amp; Hate Speech</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Targeted harassment, bullying, or coordinated attacks against individuals</li>
        <li>Hate speech based on race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, disability, religion, or national origin</li>
        <li>Doxxing (publishing private personal information without consent)</li>
        <li>Encouraging others to harass or harm someone</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-red-700">Spam &amp; Platform Manipulation</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Automated posting, bot networks, or coordinated inauthentic behavior</li>
        <li>Mass unsolicited messaging or comment spam</li>
        <li>Impersonation of other users, public figures, or organizations</li>
        <li>Artificially inflating engagement (fake likes, fake follows, engagement rings)</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ─── WHAT'S ALLOWED ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-green-700">What IS Allowed</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn is for real people connecting authentically. The following are explicitly permitted:</p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Genuine self-expression</strong> &mdash; art, photography, writing, opinions, humor, and creative content</li>
        <li><strong>Tobacco &amp; cannabis</strong> &mdash; discussion and depiction of smoking and marijuana use is allowed. This is an adults-only platform.</li>
        <li><strong>Alcohol</strong> &mdash; discussion and social content involving alcohol is allowed</li>
        <li><strong>Religious expression</strong> &mdash; sincere discussion of faith, spirituality, and religious topics is welcome</li>
        <li><strong>Criticism</strong> &mdash; criticism of ideas, public figures, companies, and institutions is allowed, including strong opinions and harsh words, as long as it doesn't become targeted harassment of private individuals</li>
        <li><strong>Profanity</strong> &mdash; swearing is allowed. This is an adult platform. Profanity is only flagged when it crosses into hate speech or targeted abuse</li>
        <li><strong>NSFW content (labeled)</strong> &mdash; artistic nudity, mature themes, and suggestive content are allowed when properly labeled as NSFW. Our AI moderation system automatically applies NSFW labels to sensitive content so users who have blur enabled won't see it unexpectedly</li>
        <li><strong>Harm reduction content</strong> &mdash; educational discussion about drug safety, addiction recovery, and harm reduction resources is permitted and encouraged</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ─── WHAT HAPPENS WHEN CONTENT IS FLAGGED ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">What Happens When Content Is Flagged</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Automatic classification</strong> &mdash; our AI system evaluates your content and assigns a classification: clean, NSFW (labeled but visible), or flagged (pending review)</li>
        <li><strong>Human review</strong> &mdash; flagged content is placed in a moderation queue for human review. A moderator examines the content and the AI's reasoning</li>
        <li><strong>Action</strong> &mdash; the moderator either approves the content (false positive), applies an NSFW label, or removes it with a reason</li>
        <li><strong>Notification</strong> &mdash; you are notified of any moderation action taken on your content, including the reason</li>
        <li><strong>Appeal</strong> &mdash; you can appeal any moderation decision through the in-app appeal process. Appeals are reviewed by a different moderator</li>
      </ol>

      <!-- ─── ACCOUNT CONSEQUENCES ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Account Consequences</h2>
      <table class="w-full mb-6 text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead><tr class="border-b"><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Severity</th><th class="text-left py-2 pr-4">Action</th><th class="text-left py-2">Examples</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Low</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Content labeled NSFW</td><td class="py-2">Suggestive imagery, strong language in specific contexts</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Medium</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Content removed + warning</td><td class="py-2">Spam, mild harassment, untagged NSFW content</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 pr-4">High</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Content removed + temporary suspension</td><td class="py-2">Hate speech, scams, doxxing, repeated violations</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Severe</td><td class="py-2 pr-4">Immediate permanent ban</td><td class="py-2">CSAM, sexual exploitation of minors, credible threats of violence</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <!-- ─── DATA & AI TRANSPARENCY ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Data &amp; AI Transparency</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
        <li>Our primary AI moderation model (<strong>LLaMA Guard</strong>) runs <strong>locally on our own server hardware</strong>. Your text content is analyzed entirely within our infrastructure and is never sent to OpenAI, Google, Microsoft, or any external LLM provider.</li>
        <li>SightEngine, our secondary layer, is a dedicated moderation-only service. Per their <a href="https://sightengine.com/policies/terms" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Terms of Service</a>, they are contractually prohibited from using your content to train machine learning models. They retain no ownership or rights to your data beyond what is needed to perform the moderation check.</li>
        <li>SightEngine is <strong>GDPR compliant</strong>, operates under a signed Data Processing Addendum, and encrypts all data in transit with TLS 1.3. Their infrastructure partners hold ISO 27001 and SOC 2 certifications.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use your content to train any AI models &mdash; not locally, and not through any third party.</li>
        <li>Moderation metadata stored in our logs is automatically deleted after 14 days. We do not retain copies of your content for moderation review beyond what is needed for the active appeal window.</li>
        <li>Our source code is publicly available for audit and transparency. We use a <a href="/licenses" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">split licensing model</a> &mdash; the mobile app is Apache 2.0, the admin panel and website are AGPL-3.0, and the core API engine uses the Business Source License 1.1 (which converts to Apache 2.0 after four years). You can review all code at <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">our repository</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ─── INFRASTRUCTURE & TECHNOLOGY ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Infrastructure &amp; Technology</h2>
      <p class="mb-6">We believe you should know exactly where your data lives and what software handles it. Here is our full stack.</p>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Hosting: Hetzner (Germany)</h3>
        <p class="mb-3">All Sojorn infrastructure runs on a dedicated server hosted by <strong>Hetzner Online GmbH</strong>, a German hosting company headquartered in Gunzenhausen, Germany. Our server is located in Hetzner's <strong>Falkenstein, Germany</strong> data center.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-sm">
          <li><strong>German jurisdiction.</strong> Hetzner is subject to German privacy law and the GDPR &mdash; not US surveillance laws, not the CLOUD Act, and not National Security Letters. Any foreign data request must go through Mutual Legal Assistance Treaties (MLATs) and German court review.</li>
          <li><strong>ISO 27001 certified.</strong> Hetzner's data centers are certified under the ISO/IEC 27001 information security management standard.</li>
          <li><strong>GDPR compliant.</strong> Hetzner operates under a Data Processing Agreement per GDPR Article 28. The German Federal Data Protection Act (BDSG) adds supplementary protections beyond the GDPR baseline.</li>
          <li><strong>Data stays in the EU.</strong> Unless otherwise specified, your data remains within the European Union and is not passed to third parties.</li>
          <li><strong>Dedicated hardware.</strong> We run on a dedicated physical server &mdash; not shared cloud instances. Your data is not co-located with other customers' workloads.</li>
          <li><strong>Encrypted in transit.</strong> All connections to our server use TLS. Internal services communicate over encrypted channels.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">Hetzner policies: <a href="https://www.hetzner.com/legal/privacy-policy/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a> &middot; <a href="https://www.hetzner.com/legal/terms-and-conditions/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Terms &amp; Conditions</a> &middot; <a href="https://www.hetzner.com/legal/data-privacy-faq/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Data Privacy FAQ</a></p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Tech Stack</h3>
        <p class="mb-3">We use a straightforward, modern stack with no third-party analytics, tracking pixels, or ad networks.</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-sm">
          <li>
            <strong>Backend: Go (Golang)</strong> &mdash; our API server is written in Go using the <a href="https://gin-gonic.com/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Gin</a> framework. Go is a compiled, statically-typed language created by Google. It runs directly on our server as a single binary with no external runtime dependencies. There is no Node.js, Python, or PHP involved in serving your data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Database: PostgreSQL</strong> &mdash; all user data, posts, messages, and moderation records are stored in <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">PostgreSQL</a>, an open-source relational database that has been actively developed for over 35 years. PostgreSQL runs locally on our server &mdash; we do not use any cloud-hosted database service (no AWS RDS, no Supabase, no Firebase). Your data never leaves our machine for storage.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Mobile App: Flutter</strong> &mdash; the Sojorn app is built with <a href="https://flutter.dev/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Flutter</a>, Google's open-source UI framework. The app communicates with our API over HTTPS and does not contain any third-party analytics SDKs, ad SDKs, or tracking libraries. Push notifications use Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM), which is the standard delivery mechanism for Android &mdash; notification tokens are stored on our server, not in any third-party analytics platform.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Media Storage: Cloudflare R2</strong> &mdash; uploaded images and videos are stored in <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/products/r2/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Cloudflare R2</a>, an S3-compatible object storage service. R2 does not charge egress fees and Cloudflare does not inspect or analyze stored content. All media URLs are signed (time-limited) so content cannot be hotlinked or accessed without authorization.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>End-to-End Encryption: X3DH + Double Ratchet</strong> &mdash; private messages and Capsule (encrypted group) conversations use the <a href="https://signal.org/docs/specifications/x3dh/" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">Extended Triple Diffie-Hellman</a> key agreement protocol, the same cryptographic foundation used by Signal. Encrypted messages cannot be read by our server, our moderators, or any third party.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Source Available</strong> &mdash; our entire codebase is publicly available. We use a <a href="/licenses" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">split licensing model</a>: the mobile app is Apache 2.0, the admin panel and website are AGPL-3.0, and the core API engine uses the BSL 1.1 (converts to Apache 2.0 after four years). Audit every line at <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline" target="_blank">gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── REPORTING ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Reporting Content</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">If you see content that violates these guidelines:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>In-app</strong> &mdash; tap the three-dot menu on any post, comment, or profile and select "Report"</li>
        <li><strong>Email</strong> &mdash; contact <a href="mailto:safety@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">safety@sojorn.net</a> with details</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">All reports are reviewed. We do not disclose the identity of reporters.</p>

      <!-- ─── CONTACT ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Safety &amp; moderation: <a href="mailto:safety@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">safety@sojorn.net</a><br>
        Privacy: <a href="mailto:privacy@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">privacy@sojorn.net</a><br>
        General: <a href="mailto:hello@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">hello@sojorn.net</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
